==Championship statistics==

===Scoring===

* First goal of the championship: Colm Cronin for Dublin against Laois (<small>''28 May 2014''</small>)
*Widest winning margin: '''30'''
**Antrim 7-17 - 1-05 Down (<small>''23 July 2014''</small>)
*Most goals in a match: '''8'''
**Antrim 7-17 - 1-05 Down (<small>''23 July 2014''</small>)
*Most points in a match: '''44'''
**Clare 5-19 - 1-25 Tipperary (<small>''16 July 2014''</small>)
*Most goals by one team in a match: '''7'''
**Antrom 7-17 - 1-05 Down (<small>''23 July 2014''</small>)
* Highest aggregate score: '''62'''
**Clare 5-19 - 1-25 Tipperary (<small>''16 July 2014''</small>)
*Lowest aggregate score: '''27'''
**Westmeath 0-13 - 2-8 Dublin (<small>''25 June 2014''</small>)
*Most goals scored by a losing team: '''3'''
**Armagh 3-7 - 3-24 Down (<small>''16 July 2014''</small>)

===Discipline===

* First red card of the championship: Willie Young for Laois against Dublin (<small>''28 May 2014''</small>)

